<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Create Test Hub</title>
    <style>
        * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

        body {
            font-family: "Segoe UI", "Trebuchet MS", sans-serif;
            min-height: 100vh;
            color: #1f2937;
            background:
                radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(255,255,255,0.3), transparent 30%),
                linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            padding: 28px 20px;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
        }

        .back-link {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 8px;
            color: white;
            text-decoration: none;
            font-weight: 800;
            margin-bottom: 22px;
        }

        .hero {
            text-align: center;
            color: white;
            margin-bottom: 34px;
        }

        .hero h1 {
            font-size: 3rem;
            font-weight: 900;
            letter-spacing: -0.05em;
            margin-bottom: 12px;
        }

        .hero p {
            max-width: 720px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            line-height: 1.7;
            opacity: 0.92;
        }

        .builder-note {
            margin-top: 18px;
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
            padding: 10px 16px;
            border-radius: 999px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.14);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
            gap: 22px;
        }

        .card {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 18px;
            padding: 28px;
            border-radius: 28px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.94);
            backdrop-filter: blur(18px);
            text-decoration: none;
            color: inherit;
            box-shadow: 0 24px 44px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.12);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.28);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease, border-color 0.3s ease;
        }

        .card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-10px);
            box-shadow: 0 30px 54px rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.16);
        }

        .reading { border-top: 8px solid #3b82f6; }
        .listening { border-top: 8px solid #10b981; }
        .writing { border-top: 8px solid #f97316; }

        .icon {
            font-size: 3.5rem;
            line-height: 1;
        }

        .card h2 {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            font-weight: 900;
            letter-spacing: -0.03em;
        }

        .card p {
            color: #64748b;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

        .feature-list {
            display: grid;
            gap: 10px;
            padding: 18px;
            border-radius: 20px;
            background: #f8fafc;
            border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
            color: #475569;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        .feature-list div {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 10px;
            font-weight: 700;
        }

        .cta {
            margin-top: auto;
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 14px 18px;
            border-radius: 999px;
            font-weight: 900;
            color: white;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
            box-shadow: 0 12px 26px rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.28);
        }

        .footer-note {
            margin-top: 24px;
            padding: 18px 20px;
            border-radius: 22px;
            background: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);
            color: white;
            line-height: 1.7;
        }

        @media (max-width: 1080px) {
            .grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .hero h1 { font-size: 2.3rem; }
        }

        /* Dark Mode Styles */
        body.dark-mode {
            background:
                radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(0,0,0,0.3), transparent 30%),
                linear-gradient(135deg, #0f172a 0%, #1e293b 100%);
            color: #e2e8f0;
        }

        body.dark-mode .back-link {
            color: #a5f4fc;
        }

        body.dark-mode .back-link:hover {
            color: #67e8f9;
        }

        body.dark-mode .hero h1 {
            color: #f1f5f9;
        }

        body.dark-mode .hero p {
            color: #cbd5e1;
        }

        body.dark-mode .builder-note {
            background: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.15);
            border-color: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.3);
            color: #cbd5e1;
        }

        body.dark-mode .card {
            background: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.95);
            box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
        }

        body.dark-mode .card h3 {
            color: #f1f5f9;
        }

        body.dark-mode .card p {
            color: #cbd5e1;
        }

        body.dark-mode .desc {
            color: #94a3b8;
        }

        body.dark-mode .footer-note {
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
            border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
            color: #cbd5e1;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <a href="/admin" class="back-link">← Back to Admin Dashboard</a>

        <section class="hero">
            <h1>Builder-Based Test Creation</h1>
            <p>Each path below opens the real builder-style authoring interface. The platform save action is layered on top, so what you create here stays aligned with the exact reading, listening, and writing builders.</p>
            <div class="builder-note">Listening audio files are uploaded to the server and stored locally instead of embedding base64 inside the saved test.</div>
        </section>

        <section class="grid">
            <a href="/create-test/reading" class="card reading">
                <div class="icon">📖</div>
                <div>
                    <h2>Reading Builder</h2>
                    <p>Use the full reading builder flow with the same tabs, passage layout, question generation tools, and export-matched renderer.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-list">
                    <div>Builder-identical authoring shell</div>
                    <div>Reading passages and question blocks</div>
                    <div>Platform save routed into the builder page</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cta">Open Reading Builder</div>
            </a>

            <a href="/create-test/listening" class="card listening">
                <div class="icon">🎧</div>
                <div>
                    <h2>Listening Builder</h2>
                    <p>Compose all four parts with the original listening builder interface while uploading audio files to the server.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-list">
                    <div>Server-side audio storage</div>
                    <div>Part-by-part authoring with pause option</div>
                    <div>Student HTML keeps direct audio URLs</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cta">Open Listening Builder</div>
            </a>

            <a href="/create-test/writing" class="card writing">
                <div class="icon">✍️</div>
                <div>
                    <h2>Writing Builder</h2>
                    <p>Author Task 1 and Task 2 in the original writing builder layout, including prompts, model answers, and the review workflow.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="feature-list">
                    <div>Task 1 and Task 2 builder parity</div>
                    <div>Review-ready student output</div>
                    <div>Platform save without losing builder styling</div>
                </div>
                <div class="cta">Open Writing Builder</div>
            </a>
        </section>

        <div class="footer-note">
            Saved tests render through the same shared exporter for student view, teacher preview, and HTML download, so the visual output stays consistent from authoring to delivery.
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
